intro.dsc: In our course, you will start from the beginning by downloading Java JDK and Android Studio. Once you have those installed, you will learn by building real applications like Instagram & Foursquare Clones! We teach you step by step and if you ever have any questions, all you have to do is post in our course discussion to receive help from Atil or Joe! Not only only will you learn with more than 15 hours of HD video, but you will also learn about designing your applications in Sketch. This will give your applications a professional touch and separate your app from all of the others! We also show you step by step how to submit your new app to the Google Play Store!

pts: By the end of our course, you will be able to create professional applications and submit them to the play store from scratch!
You will also have the skills of a professional developer who can earn thousands of dollars creating applications
Running Kotlin inside Docker container and Docker Compose
Use the most popular multithreading frameworks for Android (RxJava, Kotlin Coroutines, etc.)

preReq: Write thread-safe code of any complexity
Use the most popular multithreading frameworks for Android (RxJava, Kotlin Coroutines, etc.)
Find subtle thread-safety bugs in code
notFor: Keep the user interface responsive at all times
Prevent memory leaks in your Android applications
Manage up to hundreds of inter-dependent threads

experts.name: Pallavi Singla
experts.qlf: MBBS, MS (Obstetrician and a Gynaecologist), Fellowship in Gynae endoscopy, Fellowship in Cosmetic Gynaecology
experts.abt: Dr. Pallavi Bansal is an obstetrician and a gynaecologist. She did her medical training from PGIMS, Rohtak followed by Senior Residency from PGI, Chandigarh. She is currently practising as a Consultant Gynaecologist at Mukat Hospital & Heart Institute, Chandigarh. Her areas of interest and expertise include Gynae endoscopy and Cosmetic gynaecology along with routine obstetrics and gynaecological problems of adolescent and young women.
